Jeff Wicks, News24Durban. (Duncan Alfreds, Fin24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A man was killed when he fell from the balcony of a Point Precinct building in Durban on Friday. Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said paramedics had rushed to Signal Road in the upmarket development. &nbsp;"Paramedics arrived on the scene to find the man unresponsive and lying on the sidewalk.""The man was found to have sustained critical injuries and was pronounced deceased on the scene," Jamieson added. He said details around the man's fall remained unclear, but that police&nbsp;were investigating the incident. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.